        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:34PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sterling, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling, Atwood, St Petersburg and Reiradon Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
